<i>Posted by ToodEloo on 11-16-2002 03:14 AM:</i>

<p><b> Rules for executioner trial in PoJ</b></p>

<p>After seeing a group of 6 show up for trial and all 6 get on the list and all 6 go in 6 times, I was inspired to come up with some rules for the trials.<br />
<br />
How about the same person can't go in twice in a row.  <br />
<br />
Also, how about if a group isn't ready they get moved to the end of the list, not next on the list.<br />
<br />
So frustrating having one rude group waste literally hours of others time.<br />
<br />
Anyone else have thoughts?  Oh,  and as to how to enforce these rules, same as with any other player based rules. If the majority agree that they are fair then peer pressure is used to enforce them.<br />
<br />
  Tood Eloo</p>

<!-- END TEMPLATE: printthreadbit --><!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: printthreadbit -->
