<i>Posted by Warfust on 11-18-2002 07:26 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>I was lucky enough (/cough) to run the list for about 14 hours. It is a pain in the ass, and some folks don't like it no matter how you do it. <br />
<br />
<br />
There are people who put every person in their group on the list, and those that, at lvl53, put themselves on the list without a group and just kind of hope they get lucky. There is a lot of group jumping and helping others to give everyone a decent shot at succeeding.<br />
<br />
The solution I threatened to implement (but never did) when too many started bitching about my rules (you know, like actually being there) was that I would do it all in the raid setup. And if you did not have a full group present, as such in the raid, and were not stealing folks from other groups to complete yours, you were not on the list.<br />
<br />
<br />
As for the zerg comment….huh?<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
