<i>Posted by Carmaris on 11-21-2002 07:33 AM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>I'd been wondering about the zerg comment too...perhaps we need to define the term.<br />
<br />
To zerg something is to simply rush it with a much larger force than would be necessary if you used strategy and skill.  By zerging a mob, you're hoping that there are enough people present that 2/3 or more of your raid force can end up dead yet you still get the kill.<br />
<br />
For instance, a six man group of level 30 characters could assault a sand giant in the Oasis and have a reasonable chance at success.  However, 30 level 20's would swarm the giant, hoping to do enough damage to kill it before the last man falls.<br />
<br />
See the difference?<br />
<br />
Now, the trials are not a zerg fest.  They're not even a lemming event, because in my experience, although you may fail many times, you usually don't die a lot unless it hits the fan.  Most groups tend to fail during the 4 waves by not killing the mobs fast enough--getting killed during this part should be pretty rare.  It's only in the (making this number up) 10% or so that make it to the final mob that you're going to encounter lots of deaths...<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
